CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 25, 1958, pg. A17, reads: "Baseball Stars Visit Ken Buick - Willie Mays, left, of the San Francisco Giants, and Ernie Banks, right, star shortstop of the Chicago Clubs, who just signed fabulous contracts for 1958, visited Ken Buick Company last week-end.  Sales Manager Moe Wysocky, center, provided Mal Goode of The Courier with a new 1958 Buick Limited as transportation for these baseball stars while they were in the city.  Mr. Wysocky told Mr. Goode, 'It is a real honor to accommodate these two fine American athletes, and our staff was pleased to have them visit our place.' - Harris Photo. - Adv."
TitMainTitle: San Francisco Giants baseball player Willie Mays, sales manager Moe Wysocky, and Chicago Cubs baseball player Ernie Banks posed with 1958 Buick Limited convertible car, in Ken Buick Company with Air Born B-58 Buick sign
